				Well wisdom isnt ALL bad... even for a Mage.  It does help with certain things (not related to casting or doing Mage specific things).  My biggest gripe is this:   It's SO much easier to just go to Permafrost at level 25+ and get a Ruined Circlet (+4 INT +4 WIS) then to complete this quest and get an item with these awful stats.  To complete the quest you WASTE time running everywhere (which means you arent gaining experience), you also need to be level 30ish or higher (or a great begger in the right place at the right time), and even then you need some luck getting the freaking mobs to drop the item(s) you need.  Here's my few coppers to Verant... quest items for each class should have two major things (as far as stats go): 1. Stats that make the item stand out for the class they are intended for, above and beyond an item that is attainable by a level 35 or under without purchasing them.  2. They should all have some small, but useful effect (for the casting classes specifically).  That doesn't mean they have to be huge spells but a good utility spell on each item or on a couple items per class would be the right thing to do.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Honestly Verant... wake up and hear what your customers are saying!!  You want to give them quests that are worth their time (and money) then start being a LITTLE more customer centric!!!<BR>
